"First, I was relieved it was not a rye IPA (don't shoot, but rye isn't my thing). I've had it bottled and draft and both left a gorgeous lace. The aroma isn't anythjng to write home about and the feel is a little lighter than what it looks like (but for a black IPA its on point). I really enjoyed the flavor and the bitter ending to each sip. It's my latest crush and I am excited to drink it while this winter apocalypse continues."
