"Tasted from a 12 ounce bottle on January 24, 2015."
"Pours a very dark brown (bordering on black until you shine a light into it) with ruby hints when held to the light,  producing 3+ fingers of frothy, moderately lasting, khaki head that leaves a collar ring & patches of chunky lacing. Aroma is grapefruit, earthy floral & a little pine, with roasted notes of chocolate intermingled with hints of anise, molasses & very faint coffee. Taste is grapefruit hoppy-roast fronted but by mid-sip is citrus, Hershey's chocolate syrup & semisweet chocolate with caramel, molasses & a little coffee, in the finish it transitions to more bitter pine dominant hops backed up by citrus, smoke, & burnt malts, becoming a hop bitter/burnt chocolate malt aftertaste. There is a plastic/phenolic presence briefly, but definitely on my palate, in the finish. Alcohol is well hidden in both the nose and mouth for an 8.9 ABV; very little warmth but some alcohol bitterness and perhaps spice in the mouth. There is dark wheat malt in this but I do not pick it up in either the nose or mouth. Mouthfeel is medium to heavy with moderate carbonation, creamy & mildly chewy with a little prickle in the finish. I agree (as I often do) with Jweave, WOW & well done Founders!!!"
