"Overall - I am very glad that I had not decided to write this review until the fourth time that I had tried this beer. At first the bitterness completely overpowers the rest of the beer, but, as I've found more and more with Founder's beers and I can't help but be redundant, the more you try it, it's almost as if it has such a perfect medley of flavors that you can choose the characteristics that you want from it, it can either be a bitter, crisp, hoppy pale ale or a smooth, malty sweet dark beer with beautiful undertones of pine and roasted chestnut. By meditation one can transcend the bitterness. A definite addition to my regular rotation of craft brews when it's available."
