"BOD 9/10/14  Clear, almost black pour, that under strong light appears as a very deep dark ruby.  Normal head volume, above average retention and lacing.  Nice nose of blended hops (citrus, rind and pine) over a slight biscuit/caramel  sweetness with a spicy note. As it warms, alcohol and char notes are present.  Almost medium body with a bit of slick texture.  Normal carbonation with a bit of effervescence on the finish.  The flavor profile is a bit intense, yet well balanced with subtle complexities, for this hop forward ale.  It begins with pine and grapefruit rind hop flavors that slowly yield to a medium bitterness.  As the bitterness fades in the middle, caramel sweetness comes forward providing a well constructed balance.  As this fades, tropical hop notes, a bit of char and peppery spice notes come forward.  The finish is long and leaves you with a strong alcohol note and back of the throat burn. A sweet bitterness lingers."
""
