"O: this is an interesting beer I've never been crazy about black IPAs because usually the roast taste over powers the beer but this is very smooth and the fruit taste is dynamite it just doesn't linger like a regular IPA the malts just cut it short. it's a pretty good beer. Worth grabbing if you don't even like the style."
"Finishing off my drinking day with my least favorite style done my one of my favorite brewers.  Gotta love conflict, right?  This stuff pours a very dark black-brown topped by a finger of dark khaki foam.  Hm, you'd think darkness was a theme here...  The nose comprises pine resin, mixed greens, and light dry maple syrup.  The taste brings in more of the same, along with a strong vein of treacly roasted malts.  A good amount of bitterness pervades.  The body is a light medium, with a light moderate carbonation and a rather drying finish.  Overall, though my opinion on the style has not changed, Founders has made a black IPA that I don't hate.  I'll likely not have another, but the balance between the bittering agents (the hops and the roast) assures that at least I won't be looking back at this beer in anger (so no worries, Gallagher Brothers...)."
