"Overall, it is hard to find a Founders release that disappoints.  With this one we found a hugely surprising degree of bittering char and leathery bite from the massive malt character.  Unlike your typical black IPA, however, we missed that overly sweetened hop profile to bring you into that beautiful blend that you look for.  With that said, this was a very simple beer.  To compare, last years “Inspired Artist” took on that fantastic balance, with fruitiness of hops big enough to meet the dark malt profile.  Here, with a presumably imperial version of that recipe, the char takes us to a whole new level of darkness that lets little escape beyond it.  We have been sitting on this one a couple weeks longer than most everyone else, but we don’t feel that the hops would fade much in that time to allow for such a presentation."
