"A fingers worth of ultra rich, ultra dense and ultra creamy light khaki colored froth...  At first glance this one appears mostly still, but under closer examination this one is bursting with quick carbonation throughout...  The color walks a fine line between dark brown and black...  It is also fairly translucent, especially when back lit...  A good bit of froth clings to the sides of the glass...  A fairly subdued but pleasant aroma of lightly roasted malt and faint piney hop resins...  The aroma is a perfect predictor of the palate...  The lightly roasted malt and piney hop presence compete for prominence and partake in an enjoyable dance...  The mouthfeel is utterly exquisite and outstanding...  Medium bodied...  Insanely rich...  Insanely smooth...  A bit chewy...  Lit carbonation...  This one is a world class American Black Ale...  It hides its 8.9% ABV...  When Founders decided to add a Black IPA to their year-round line-up, you would expect it to be excellent, but this one exceeds those lofty expectations..."
