"O) very very good founders has been kicking butt the last few years and this beer is no exception!"
""
""
"Bottle. Pours quite dark. Initially didn't think it was going to but once all the liquid settles in the glass, it's hard to find much light entering this beer. Light tan head. Stringy lacing. Aroma is interesting. Huge grapefruit presence. The dark malts are also important. I get subtle whiffs of smoke and anise. Heavily hoppy but still dependent upon its rich dark maltiness. The bitterness crashes upon the tongue. The hops are piney and coercive. They don't have much flavor depth; mostly just pure buttering effect. The sweetness brings forth more complexity. Rock candy, brown sugar, roast. Finishes with some wheat character. This beer is beyond bitter. Aspirin-like bitterness. I can't recall a more bitter beer in recent memory. Body isn't overly heavy; I was expecting more and I am actually happy with its forgiving heftiness. If there is any alcohol in the flavor it's hidden behind he fact that my tongue is absolutely blown out by the bitterness. Well carbonated. Well made, caustic bitterness, has its intricacies. May take a while to get through this 4 pack. The combo of roast and nearly toxic bitterness has me down on this beer. Probably a brew I would have liked more early on in my craft beer voyage."
""
""
""
""
"Overall – A very delicious and nicely hopped black IPA with a very nice balance between hop, roast, dark flavors, and sweeter tastes.  This is a very enjoyable brew!!  Founders makes yet another fantastic one here."
