"Overall / Drinkability:  I think the name is very fitting.  You need to be a hop lover for this beer to begin with, and then you will still do some penance for drinking the beer.  It's a strangely pleasurable pain with the hop bitterness.  I like bitterness and it comes through in this beer in spades.  The alcohol is dangerously well hidden; I did not detect it or start to feel it until the end of the 1st glass.  And since I was staying for awhile and having a pizza as well, a second one was a welcome event, even though it dealt out additional penance to my tongue.  A very good beer and I'm glad I had two over a long meal with friends.  Good to look at and strong in flavor.  I've done my penance and don't mind."
