"Pours a beautiful midnight black with a deep purple hue.  Creamy, one finger head which settles to a lingering frothy cap.  Leaves a good layer of lace around the glass after each sip.  Smells fantastic.  Hint of alcohol, a bit of citrus from the hops, and a slight aroma similar to a RIS.  The bitterness is perfect and well balanced by its hop character.  Very pleasant with a slight smokey flavor as it goes down.  This is right up there with Surly Blakkr, which I love.  Seriously considering letting it in my top 10 brews list...  A very good beer.  I recommend trying it for anyone who likes hops, bitterness, stouts, and medium to full-bodied beers.  Founders does a fine job yet again."
