"Very dark, nearly black color – some deep red highlights shining through towards the bottom of the glass.  The head is small and sticky, leaving nice clusters of lace on the glass.  Aroma is chocolaty, developing a fruity greenness as it warms.  Instantly chocolaty in the mouth and surprisingly light on the hops.  I was expecting bold, spicy pine and floral/citrus battling it out with the malt, but what I got was lots of cocoa and a mild leafy citrus presence. Every one of the 100 IBU seems to be in full effect however, giving some edge to an otherwise creamy, medium-plus body.  Despite the lack of hops, I actually enjoyed this as more of a bitter chocolaty malty beer.  Easy drinking for its strength too.  I think I’ll need to try one from the bottle to see how it compares."
