"I'm always happy to try a new beer from Founders. I picked up a bottle of this one after trying it at my weekly beer tasting. Black IPAs are not my favorite style, and this one lacks the complexity of Stone's SSRA (or that 15th Anniversary beer Stone made that was simply divine - anyone else remember that one?). Nevertheless, I really like the balance between roast and hops that Founders has struck here. It's like the Roast Party holds 58 Senate seats, the Hops Party holds 36, and the Malt Party holds the other 6. However, as we all know, these parties somehow work together just fine."
