"12 ounce bottle, bottled 9/10/2014.  Served in a DFH IPA glass, the beer pours very dark brown with about an inch light tan head.  Head retention and lacing are both good.  The brew smells like roasted malt, pine hops and citrusy hops.  It tastes like citrusy (citrus peel, grapefruit) and pine hops, roasted malt, coffee, bittersweet chocolate, and some earthiness.  Nice bitter finish.  Mouthfeel/body is medium, it's a bit coating with a moderate amount of carbonation.  It's also easy enough and enjoyable to drink.  Overall I liked this, but for whatever reason I expected it to be better.  Maybe I just expect more out of Founders than I do most other breweries.  And at $13.99 a 4-pack, to me it seems pricey.  Still, it's certainly worth trying if you've never had it before."
