"Second review, poured into a pint glass: pours so dark brown that it looks black, like a stout with a 2 finger foamy tan head that was full of tiny bubble and faded very slowly, leaving excellent foamy lacing and rings as it went down, plus a nice layer on top. Smell from the glass has more herbal notes like mint and tea leaf mixed with the roasted/burnt malt and rich coffee notes. The charred grains and hoppy sweetness make for a wonderful smelling nose. Tastes great, and certainly not less filling; the chocolate, burnt malt, coffee and smoky bitterness merge and balance quite well with the bitter piney hop and grapefruit flavors. The alcohol is caught up in the cyclone of flavors and has no bearing on the overall appeal of this brew, which has a kick that sneaks up on you. I’ve had several of these over the past 2 weeks and this is another great beer from Founders that I highly recommend. It's another great Black IPA that was released this year and worthy of mention within the class of Stone's Sublimely Self-Righteous Ale."
