"Poured from a bottle into a shaker pint, the beer is jet black, with mahogany highlights, and a fluffy, light, foamy, light tan colored head that quickly settles out into a filmy surface coating. Aromas of resinous pitch, bitter hops, sweet citrus, wood and pepper spice, and a hint of roast and smoke in the backbone. Very hop heavy nose. Flavors are extremely resinous and heavy grapefruit forward, providing an absolute blast of tart and bitter on the palate. Wow! Solid roast backbone, with some hints of coffee and chocolate, but it's all about the resin, grapefruit, pine, citrus, and bitterness in this one. Hopheads rejoice! The body is soft, mid-range, but supports the palate perfectly. Very bitter, citrus heavy aftertaste, with lingering resinous notes. The finish is smooth, slightly dry, and light, and the drying bitterness lingers on for a bit. This is a beast. A fun hopped exercise for your palate."
